The president hesitated for three months, but did not come up with a better idea and so he cheated the general on 10,000 soldiers.
From Europe, he has pressed the pledge for another 5,000, even though he himself originally expected at least 10,000.
Most problematic of the entire Obama strategy is his plan to withdraw troops from Afghanistan in as little as 18 months, and to complete this process within three years. The whole Obama doctrine leaves more questions than answers.
Some doubt that the half-assed uprising will have the same effect as the measure in Iraq.
Even in spite of the fraternal war of recent years, Iraq society is relatively well structured, its leaders honor the values.
The Afghan situation is characterised by the contraindication - no one can rely on anyone and no agreements will be made.
Under these conditions, it is difficult to prepare the Afghan security forces, who are used to changing their minds every day.
The political institutions, even if they were formally founded correctly, remain only seeming structures behind which patriarchal tribal relations will continue to grow.
The balancing of interests between the different ethnic groups is unusually complicated, especially because of the opaque nature of the conditions that further complicate the Pakistani and Iranian influences.
It is also very unrealistic to establish a "acting state", which is the minimalist goal of the entire operation.
Time horizon of the Obama strategy alienated by its volunteerism
Over the past eight years, the situation in Afghanistan has only worsened further and is now on the brink of an explosion.
They believe that the little soldiers who have broken into the war cry about the "early return" create a miracle here can only create a truly romantic soul that is not impressed by facts.
From the political point of view, the date setting for the troop withdrawal is purely irresponsible, because the Taliban will take this as the indirect confession of American defeat.
